<TITLE> 3rd div football rolls Wednesday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 27 (bdnews24.com)  The Citcell 3rd Division Football League starts on Wednesday at Birsreshtha Shaheed Mostafa Kamal Stadium with 18 teams vying for the title. "It is such a stage where the young footballers across the country get chances to prove themselves and we believe these youngsters will represent the national team in future," BFF vice president Manzoor Hossain Malu told a press conference at Bangabandhu National Stadium Tuesday. As many as 18 teams, split into two groups, will play the round-robin league and later top four teams from each group will advance into the eight-team super league. The champions and runners-up will be promoted to the Second Division League while two bottom teams will be relegated to the Pioneer Football League. BFF technical director Shahidur Rahman Chowdhury Shantu will inaugurate the league by the match between the Muslim Institute and Bangladesh Krira Shikkha Protisthan. Shawkat Ali Khan Jahangir, BFF vice president, M Selim Khan, secretary of the third division league committee, Asfaruzzaman Suhrab, coordinator of the league and Atiq Akbar, deputy manager, event and sponsorship of Citycell, were among others present. bd
